Abdomen (
Fig. 5
). Male 5 th ventrite evenly strongly convex, with weak depression at apical part. Apical edge of male 5 th ventrite almost straight, in females half-round.

Subgenital segments of male (
Fig. 20
). Anterior edge of 8 th tergite straight, without depression. 8 th sternite divided into two plates. 9 th sternite with robust apodeme carrying a massive curved caput.

